<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2531">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-2531 mb-requirement-id-2532">
        (a) Show that you have had an average grade of B or higher (80 percent
        or higher) for one term or semester. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/pZMXqaY-bYc" target="_blank"
          >How to Do Better in School (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-2531 mb-requirement-id-2535">
        (b) Show that for one term or semester you have improved your school
        grades over the previous period. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TjPFZaMe2yw" target="_blank"
          >How to Study (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2536">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do TWO of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-2536 mb-requirement-id-2537">
        (a) Make a list of educational places located where you live (other than
        schools). Visit one, and report on how you used the place for
        self-education. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MHo928fd2wE" target="_blank"
          >Why Do We Have Museums (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-2536 mb-requirement-id-2538">
        (b) With your counselor's and your parent or guardian's approval,
        interview two professionals (other than teachers or other professionals
        at your school) with established careers. Find out where they were
        educated, what training they received, and how their education and
        training have helped prepare them for the career they have chosen. Find
        out how they continue to educate themselves. Discuss what you find out
        with your counselor. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/RaSoVVF18n8?si=wbVez7VytPC0E0es"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Have a Great Coffee Chat (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-2536 mb-requirement-id-2539">
        (c) Using a daily planner, show your counselor how you keep track of
        assignments and activities, and discuss how you manage your time.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/9z35XeolxMU?si=haH_-yZvpcaTXy05"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Use Your Planner: Time-Management Tricks for Better Grades
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/ybb3h4re8kU" target="_blank"
          >My Daily Planner (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-2536 mb-requirement-id-2541">
        (d) Discuss the advantages and disadvantages of the different methods of
        research available to you for school assignments, such as the library,
        books and periodicals, and the internet. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/RH3Z9BZryd8?si=hszmMA4edfUrH0gA"
          target="_blank"
          >The Internet vs the Library (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/1iVcFKAFu2E?si=3ZZUS2aXuxu3s_A9"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Use AI in School Without Cheating (Video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2543">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Get a note from the principal of your school (or another school official
      named by the principal) that states that during the past year your
      behavior, leadership, and service have been satisfactory.<br /><br /><b
        >Note: </b
      >If you are home-schooled or your school environment does not include a
      principal, you may obtain a note from a counterpart such as your parent or
      guardian.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2544">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-2544 mb-requirement-id-2545">
        (a) Show that you have taken part in an extracurricular school activity,
        and discuss with your counselor the benefits of participation and what
        you learned about the importance of teamwork. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_YrIAc3YL3E" target="_blank"
          >What Extracurriculars Should You Do? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-2544 mb-requirement-id-2546">
        (b) Discuss your participation in a school project during the past
        semester where you were a part of a team. Tell about the positive
        contributions you made to the team and the project. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GZnvHzivMkQ" target="_blank"
          >How to Be a Great Team Player (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zdAfzLry85I" target="_blank"
          >How to Be a Team Player To Succeed (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2547">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-2547 mb-requirement-id-2548">
        (a) Write a report of 250 to 300 words about how the education you
        receive in school will be of value to you in the future and how you will
        continue to educate yourself in the future. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UK4hir5lVXg" target="_blank"
          >Personal Narrative (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-2547 mb-requirement-id-2549">
        (b) Write a report of 250 to 300 words about two careers that interest
        you and how specific classes and good scholarship in general will help
        you achieve your career goals. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o22BiMAMKPA" target="_blank"
          >Informative Writing (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
